ChatGPT said:

You're hitting a common ERESOLVE conflict due to the latest react@19.1.0 not matching peer dependencies like @testing-library/react@13.4.0, which still expects React 18.

We can fix this easily by doing one of the following:

✅ Recommended Fix (Use --legacy-peer-deps)

powershell
npx create-react-app client --template cra-template-pwa --legacy-peer-deps

This bypasses strict peer dependency checks and lets everything install without error.

🚫 Alternative (Downgrade React — not recommended right now)

We could manually install React 18, but since React 19 is stable and you’re not depending on advanced test runners immediately, just bypassing the peer checks is best.

🔍 Why This Happens

React 19 just launched, but many community packages (like @testing-library/*) haven't officially added ^19.x to their peerDependencies yet — even though they work just fine.
